genresAdvancedInfo.name: swamp blues
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This genre of music emerged from the swamps of Louisiana and Mississippi. It's a blend of traditional blues with a touch of southern soul and R&B. The music is characterized by its raw and gritty sound, with lyrics that often tell stories of hardship and struggle. Swamp blues artists often use slide guitar and harmonica to create a haunting, atmospheric sound that captures the essence of the swamp.
